           xmlns:navigation="clr-namespace:System.Windows.Controls;assembly=System.Windows.Controls.Navigation"
           d:DesignWidth="640" d:DesignHeight="480"
           Title="ViewPanelSampleDesc Page">
    <Grid x:Name="LayoutRoot">
        <TextBlock>
            View panels are typically bound with SelectedIndex, a parameter found in Controls like ToggleButtonBar, etc..
            <LineBreak/>
            Selecting the ToggleButtonBar will trigger the view for that particular selection. The view will occupy the entire available screen.
            <LineBreak/>
            All the views are stacked on top of each other, and the current selected view is displayed.
            <LineBreak/>
            This is an alternative to the “Tabbed” view. The advantage here is that more of the screen is displayed as opposed <LineBreak/>to a typical tabbed view wherein the Tabs appear on the left side of the screen occupying a row to display the tabs.            
            <LineBreak/>
            
        </TextBlock>
    </Grid>
</navigation:Page>
